onLineSrc.orDesc: Email drc@oregonmetro.gov or call 503-797-1742 for further instructions.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: Major rivers and water bodies derived from Metro's Riv_poly data layer. Includes: the Columbia, Willamette, Sandy, Clackamas and Lewis Rivers; Lake Oswego; Smith, Bybee, Vancouver and Sturgeon Lakes.

graphOver.bgFileDesc: Rivers and streams shown with topography.

LegConsts.useLimit: The information in this file was derived from digital databases on Metro's GIS. Care was taken in the creation of this file. Metro cannot accept any responsibility for errors, omissions, or positional accuracy. There are no warranties, expressed or implied.

Consts.useLimit: This database and GIS data are made available under the Open Database License (ODbL v1) and Database Content License (DbCL v1). See http://www.oregonmetro.gov/rlis-live.

report.measDesc: Same as Metro's Riv_poly data layer. The Riv_poly layer was intially registered to the US Geological Survey (USGS) 7.5 minute quadrangles, and then adjusted visually at approximately 1:10000 using the 1998 Spencer Gross aerial photography. Where photography was not available or banks and streambeds obscured, the USGS quad topography was used. Some of the major streams are registered to the tax lot map.

prcStep.stepDesc: Derived from Metros Riv_poly data layer which is an updated river and water body data layer of the Metro region created by using the previous Metro river and water body layer (an enhanced USGS hydrography layer which had been adjusted to taxlots). River and water body banks were adjusted or digitized at approximately 1:10000 using the 1998 Spencer Gross aerial photography. Where photography was not available or banks and riverbeds obscured, the USGS quad topography was used. The dataset has not been field checked.
Changed native SDE storage precision from low to high
Projection information (.prj file), compatible with ArcGIS 8.1, was added to the layer.
Incorporated Clean Water Services line work in much of the Tualatin River subbasin.
